HEADWORD: Stirrer
<hw>Stir"rer</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>One who, or that
which, stirs something; also, one who moves about, especially after
sleep; <as>as, an early <ex>stirrer</ex></as>.</def>
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Stirrer up</b></col>, <cd>an instigator or inciter.</cd>
<au>Atterbury.</au></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Stirring</ent>⟦br⟧
